A library that makes a very common task quite a bit easier. It's used for persisting and applying various types of application settings. 

Basically you would configure the library with a few lines of code, and then just tell it which properties of which objects need to be persistent (survive a shutdown).

No more copying data from .config/.settings files to objects and back again to make the data survive an application shutdown.

The library is tiny (under 500 LOC), very customizable and provides many extension points, but comes with all the basic stuff built in. 

The source repository is on github, and there is an article describing it on codeproject. The article is a bit dated, but some new how-to articles will be available soon.
summary: Persist and retrieve boring data (window locations and sizes, config settings, last entered credentials) the easy way.

Spire.Presentation for .NET support PPT, PPS, PPTX and PPSX presentation formats. It provides functions such as managing text, image, shapes, tables, animations, audio and video on slides. It also support exporting presentation slides to EMF, JPG, PDF format etc.

description: With Broadcast, a single object can communicate with multiple objects in a non-generic manor, without knowing that the objects exist. The implementations within .NET such as the IObserver and IObservable pattern are a very cumbersome subscription model for method invocation. The solution .NET provides is not very elegant and forces your application to be tightly bound to the objects. Broadcast aims to decouple objects, providing an easier path for developers to make their application more maintainable.
summary: With Broadcast, a single object can communicate with multiple objects in a non-generic manor, without knowing that the objects exist.

With Broadcast, a single object can communicate with multiple objects in a non-generic manor, without knowing that the objects exist. The implementations within .NET such as the IObserver and IObservable pattern are a very cumbersome subscription model for method invocation. The solution .NET provides is not very elegant and forces your application to be tightly bound to the objects. Broadcast aims to decouple objects, providing an easier path for developers to make their application more maintainable.
summary: With Broadcast, a single object can communicate with multiple objects in a non-generic manor, without knowing that the objects exist.

A library that makes a very common task quite a bit easier. It's used for persisting and applying various types of application settings. 

Basically you would configure the library with a few lines of code, and then just tell it which properties of which objects need to be persistent (survive a shutdown).

No more copying data from .config/.settings files to objects and back again to make the data survive an application shutdown.

The library is tiny (under 500 LOC), very customizable and provides many extension points, but comes with all the basic stuff built in. 

The source repository is on github, and there is an article describing it on codeproject. The article is a bit dated, but some new how-to articles will be available soon.
summary: Persist and retrieve boring data (window locations and sizes, config settings, last entered credentials) the easy way.

O template de Enterprise Library Data Access apresenta de forma estruturada para os aplicativos, utilizando o método SOLID, que visa simplificar o desenvolvimento de tarefas que implementam a funcionalidade de acesso a banco de dados.

Já com os templates estruturados os aplicativos podem usar esta package de aplicativo em uma variedade de situações, tais como a leitura de dados para exibição, a transferências de dados através de camadas de aplicação, e apresentação de dados alterados de volta para o sistema de banco de dados.

Acesse a documentação para mais detalhes:

http://limup.com.br/documentacao-enterpriselibrary-data-aprendendo-a-utilizar-de-forma-rapida/
